title: Dj Sona skin crashes the game
body: In the last 3 games every time i play with and only with Dj Sona my game crashes i've tried with other chapmions and nothing happend when i play with Dj Sona my game get's to the loading screen then crashes and the Client starts to repair itself and this keeps going until the game ends and i tried this even in the practice tool please look into it Riot

replies.body:
Hi! 

Sorry about the trouble. D: This seems a bit peculiar. I'm not able to repro this on my side of things. Would you be able to help me out by giving me a bit more info? 

What OS are you using/How much RAM? 

In addition, would you be able to provide me with your R3d logs from any of the games where you're crashing?  Each file appears like this: [yyyy-mm-ddT15-40-03] _r3dlog.txt, where yyyy-mm-dd is the date of the match played.

**You can find them here:** C:\Riot Games\League of Legends\Logs\GameLogs, under the time and date stamped folder for the game in which you had issues. 

Thanks a bunch!

Edition: Win10 Pro
Version: 1709
Os build: 16299.309

RAM i have 4 GB Ram (3GB are usable)

 As for the R3d file i was not sure which one of them was the right one so i've gone to the practice tool and took Sona with Dj Sona skin then entered the game loaded then crashed at the loading screen then I entered in that folder and in its R3d but i couldn't paste here everything that was in it so i decided to  reply twice to show the hole thing sorry if I did this wrong but i don't know any other way I hope i was able to help and not make things more confusing

Thanks for the reply!

Thank you so much! This is super helpful for us. <3 I know there had been issues with not having enough RAM, but I don't know if this is applying to you. Could you/have you also tried updating any graphics drivers and lemme know if that helps? 

I'm going to comb through the r3d logs in the meantime. :)

I update my drivers with one that just came out few hours ago and then tested Sona with her skin again and it works.
 Thanks a lot! Sorry for bothering you.

Phew, okay! That makes me feel a lot better about all of this. We're still going to go through logs/check some config set ups on our side, but I'm glad she's playable for you again. :) Not a bother at all, I'm happy I could help troubleshoot for ya. If you experience this again, don't hesitate to ping me in this thread. 

{{sticker:sona-playing}}
